Storages in AngularJS
-

    - AngularJS Supports the Two Types of Storages.

    1. localStorage

    2. sessionStorage


    - ngStorage is the predefined module used to with the Storages.

    - ngStorage Module Supports Two Objects.

        1.$localStorage

        2.$sessionStorage

    - "$localStorage"  used to work with the localStorage

    - $sessionStorage used to work with the sessionStorage

   - we can store the data in the form key&value pairs.